{"name":"Charizard artwork Pokemon Base Set Booster Pack TCG 4th PRINT UK (Base 2000) ENGLISH #00001-NFT","description":"Factory Sealed Pokemon Base Set Booster Pack with Charizard artwork ENGLISH from 4th print for UK with 1999-2000 copywrites with long seal.

Original Pokemon Base Set published by Wizards of the Coast. Made in UK. 
International Nintendo Licensed product.

Booster contains 11 cards from Pokemon TCG Base Set. 
They come from the Polish distribution by Hasbro company (as the sticker says). These are cards from UK distribution, all are in English. 

IMPORTANT! Not all cards have "1999-2000" but cards with Polish stickers have the greatest chances for this because it is the latest print of Base Set.

This is precisely: UNLIMITED U.K. ONLY VERSION also known as Base 2000, 
This version of the Base Set is very similar to the "Unlimited Edition With Shadow" except for a 2 small differences. It was also printed especially for the U.K. Market and was distributed in Poland too. One difference is that the printing seems to be brighter or lighter than the other versions. The other difference is the Copyright text at the bottom of each card, on this set it can reads: "1995, 96, 98 Nintendo, Creatures, GAMEFREAK C 1999-2000 Wizards". 
FINDING THIS VERSION OF THE BASE SET IS QUITE RARE (even in the UK) and a lot of people don't even know of its existence. This set also includes a 1st Edition Machamp, as does every other Base Set.

Cards printed right before the release of Base Set 2 can have the year 2000 included in their copyright notices. These cards are known as "4th issue" cards, and are also rarer than the "unlimited" print. Certain "4th issue" cards have slightly brighter color than the other prints.

These cards are no longer in print and they are becoming more valuable.","image":"https://ipfs.moralis.io:2053/ipfs/QmWkMMPUG5EhjZUm8f6Wf4TbPDQTmAA4avPRjUWd9rhrB8","attributes":[{"trait_type":"BRAND","value":"Pokemon"},{"trait_type":"MANUFACTURER","value":"Wizards of the Coast"},{"trait_type":"TYPE","value":"Pokemon TCG with NFT"},{"trait_type":"SET","value":"Base Set"},{"trait_type":"PRINT","value":"4th Print UK (Base 2000)"},{"trait_type":"LANGUAGE","value":"English"},{"trait_type":"RESELLER","value":"Pokemons.Collection"},{"trait_type":"Physically Backed","value":"Yes"}]}

tokenData.name: Charizard artwork Pokemon Base Set Booster Pack TCG 4th PRINT UK (Base 2000) ENGLISH #00001-NFT
tokenData.description:
Factory Sealed Pokemon Base Set Booster Pack with Charizard artwork ENGLISH from 4th print for UK with 1999-2000 copywrites with long seal.

Original Pokemon Base Set published by Wizards of the Coast. Made in UK. 
International Nintendo Licensed product.

Booster contains 11 cards from Pokemon TCG Base Set. 
They come from the Polish distribution by Hasbro company (as the sticker says). These are cards from UK distribution, all are in English. 

IMPORTANT! Not all cards have "1999-2000" but cards with Polish stickers have the greatest chances for this because it is the latest print of Base Set.

This is precisely: UNLIMITED U.K. ONLY VERSION also known as Base 2000, 
This version of the Base Set is very similar to the "Unlimited Edition With Shadow" except for a 2 small differences. It was also printed especially for the U.K. Market and was distributed in Poland too. One difference is that the printing seems to be brighter or lighter than the other versions. The other difference is the Copyright text at the bottom of each card, on this set it can reads: "1995, 96, 98 Nintendo, Creatures, GAMEFREAK C 1999-2000 Wizards". 
FINDING THIS VERSION OF THE BASE SET IS QUITE RARE (even in the UK) and a lot of people don't even know of its existence. This set also includes a 1st Edition Machamp, as does every other Base Set.

Cards printed right before the release of Base Set 2 can have the year 2000 included in their copyright notices. These cards are known as "4th issue" cards, and are also rarer than the "unlimited" print. Certain "4th issue" cards have slightly brighter color than the other prints.

These cards are no longer in print and they are becoming more valuable.
